<item>
            <title>[LU-14210] DNE3: &quot;lfs migrate -m&quot; should allow-non-recursive migration</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14210</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be useful, and probably more intuitive, if &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs migrate -m&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; only migrated the specified directory and required a &quot;&lt;tt&gt;-r&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; option to recursively migrate the subdirectory tree.  Alternately, &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs migrate -d -m&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; could be used to migrate only the specified directory. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="61979">LU-14210</key>
            <summary>DNE3: &quot;lfs migrate -m&quot; should allow-non-recursive migration</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=11310&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Improvement</type>
